## Proposal

### Please re-state the problem that we are trying to solve in this issue.

When opening the emoji picker via the context menu it looks like it belongs to another message instead of the one that the context menu was opened for.
### What is the root cause of that problem?

The emoji picker opens at the top right position of the context menu and has a smaller height, so that it will be placed above the message that the context menu was previously opened on.

In `src/components/Reactions/QuickEmojiReactions/index.js` the anchor origin is set to TOP, RIGHT
```
    const onPressOpenPicker = (openPicker) => {
        openPicker(contextMenuRef.current.contentRef.current, {
            horizontal: CONST.MODAL.ANCHOR_ORIGIN_HORIZONTAL.RIGHT,
            vertical: CONST.MODAL.ANCHOR_ORIGIN_VERTICAL.TOP,
        });
    };
```

### What changes do you think we should make in order to solve the problem?
<!-- DO NOT POST CODE DIFFS -->

1. Updating `src/components/Reactions/QuickEmojiReactions/index.js` with the anchor origin set to BOTTOM, LEFT
```
    const onPressOpenPicker = (openPicker) => {
        openPicker(contextMenuRef.current.contentRef.current, {
            horizontal: CONST.MODAL.ANCHOR_ORIGIN_HORIZONTAL.LEFT,
            vertical: CONST.MODAL.ANCHOR_ORIGIN_VERTICAL.BOTTOM,
        });
    };
```
2. Implementing the corresponding logic so that the proper anchor position is calculated (currently LEFT, BOTTOM does not have an implementation) in `src/libs/calculateAnchorPosition.ts` (the implementation there currently seems odd anyway):
```
export default function calculateAnchorPosition(anchorComponent: View, anchorOrigin?: AnchorOrigin) ...
    // ...
        anchorComponent.measureInWindow((x, y, width, height) => {
            // ...

            if (anchorOrigin?.vertical === CONST.MODAL.ANCHOR_ORIGIN_VERTICAL.BOTTOM && anchorOrigin?.horizontal === CONST.MODAL.ANCHOR_ORIGIN_HORIZONTAL.LEFT) {
                return resolve({horizontal: x, vertical: y + height + (anchorOrigin?.shiftVertical ?? 0)});
            }

   // ...
```

